Package: qeli
Version: 0.7.7
Architecture: amd64
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Qeli Team <team@qeli.dev>
Homepage: https://qeli.dev
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.34), libgcc-s1, iptables, iproute2, libcap2-bin
Suggests: systemd-resolved
Description: Obfuscated VPN with custom protocol and traffic masking
 A point-to-point VPN with a custom TLS-like handshake, ChaCha20-Poly1305
 encryption, traffic obfuscation (padding, fragmentation, heartbeat),
 split-tunnel routing, DNS-over-tunnel and multi-queue TUN. The server pushes
 MTU / routes / DNS to clients. One binary serves both roles: `qeli server`
 and `qeli client`.
 .
 After install, copy /etc/qeli/server.conf.example to /etc/qeli/server.conf,
 edit it (flat-INI), then `systemctl enable --now qeli`.
